The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 28 November is 111,962 (12,904.3 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 23 November, there were 5,476 new confirmed cases (631.1 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 16 November, there were 5,003 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 9% (473 extra cases).
